Remove Ads
* This task disables Microsoft Advertising ID, which is used to track user behavior and display targeted ads. * It also removes ads from Windows Search and Microsoft Edge. * This task helps to improve user privacy and reduce clutter on the system.

data.name: textBox3.Text
data.value:
Disable Tracking
* This task disables telemetry, which is used to collect user data and track system behavior. * It also disables Cortana, Windows Tips, and Windows Feedback. * This task helps to improve user privacy and reduce data collection.

data.name: textBox4.Text
data.value:
Optimize Windows
* This task disables unnecessary services, such as Windows Search. * It also adjusts power settings to improve system performance. * Additionally, it disables animations and optimizes disk performance. * This task helps to improve system performance and reduce battery drain.

data.name: textBox6.Text
data.value:
Windows System File Checker (SFC) is a built-in utility in Windows that scans for and repairs corrupted or missing system files. It helps ensure the integrity of your operating system by verifying the files against known good versions and restoring them when necessary.
What it does: Scans for corrupted or missing system files: SFC examines protected system files, comparing them to the versions stored in a cache or the original installation source.
Restores corrupted files: If it finds discrepancies, SFC replaces the corrupted files with good copies, either from the cache or the installation source.
Helps with stability: By repairing these files, SFC can resolve issues like crashes, freezes, and other system instability caused by corrupted files.

data.name: textBox2.Text
data.value:
Uninstall Bloat Programs
* This task uninstalls pre-installed games on the system, such as Solitaire and Minecraft. * It also uninstalls Microsoft Office, Windows Recall, and Microsoft Copilot. * This task helps to free up disk space and reduce clutter on the system. * You choose what programs to remove from your computer.

data.name: textBox5.Text
data.value:
Winget Updater
The Windows Package Manager (also known as winget) is a free and open-source package manager designed by Microsoft for Windows 10 and Windows 11. It consists of a command-line utility and a set of services for installing applications. Independent software vendors can use it as a distribution channel for their software packages.
Overview The winget tool supports installers based on EXE, MSIX, and MSI. The public Windows Package Manager Community repository hosts manifest files for supported applications in YAML format. In September 2020, Microsoft added the ability to install applications from the Microsoft Store and a command auto-completion feature.
To reduce the likelihood of non-Microsoft-approved software, including malicious software, making its way into the repository and onto the target machine, Windows Package Manager uses Microsoft SmartScreen, static analysis, SHA256 hash validation and other processes.
The winget client source code and the community manifest repository are licensed under MIT License and hosted on GitHub
